VALUES ('aeb2aa06-22b3-437a-8974-d3090537693f', 'Which choice most accurately describes how the text develops its central claim?', 'Archaeologists at site 100229 discovered that pottery shards contained residue of fermented grain, suggesting the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than daily meals. Layer analysis placed the shards in a ceremonial plaza rather than domestic kitchens, and nearby hearths showed feasting debris concentrated on solstice dates. Chemical tests identified compounds consistent with controlled fermentation but not with large-scale storage for everyday consumption. Nevertheless, subsequent fieldwork revealed limitations that the opening account had treated as settled fact. The team compared the findings with neighboring settlements where grain storage pits dominated the record. That contrast supports the interpretation that brewing here marked special occasions and social bonding. The passage invites readers to connect material evidence with inferred cultural practice without claiming certainty about every recipe', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It outlines a widely held assumption, introduces research challenging its universal application, and clarifies how practitioners should interpret the moderated conclusion throughout overall in sum in","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (A). Correct (A). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"B","text":"It describes only the final paragraph''s policy recommendation without accounting for the theoretical setup and evidentiary middle the passage develops before reaching that recommendation overall in sum.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"C","text":"It attributes personal ambition to the author instead of analyzing how the text moves from observation to qualified generalization across successive sentences in sum in context, rather than importing","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."},{"id":"D","text":"It asserts that the author abandons the central inquiry midway, when the passage instead deepens that inquiry through concession and counterevidence in later sentences in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
Focus on {{yellow:consistent}} in the passage. The structure item asks you to identify the passage organization before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Match structure to purpose
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On medium items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Confirm the description
Choice A is correct: It outlines a widely held assumption, introduces research challenging its universal application, and clarifies how practitioners should interpret the moderated ….

Distractor analysis:
- B: [Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory.
- C: [Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans.
- D: [Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops.', NULL, 'Craft and Structure', 'Text Structure and Purpose', 'reading_writing', 'craft', 'TSP', NULL, 'medium', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_subtype":"structure","rw_format":"passage_mc","generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","regen_seed_offset":100000,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now());
