VALUES ('59f58fe1-2db0-4b14-9c55-ae773a990fd8', 'Which choice best characterizes the text''s rhetorical structure?', 'Psychologists testing memory task 100230 reported that participants who slept eight hours recalled word lists more accurately than those who stayed awake, even when both groups studied equally long. The awake group was kept in a quiet lounge with books and puzzles to prevent napping, yet their recall still lagged behind the sleep group on both immediate and delayed tests. Brain-imaging subsamples showed differences in hippocampal activity during retrieval, aligning with theories that sleep consolidates declarative memories. The researchers caution that the study measured short lists under lab conditions and may not generalize to complex real-world learning. By contrast, later analysts argued that the initial synthesis overlooked boundary conditions essential to interpretation. Still, the controlled comparison isolates sleep as the key variable because study time,', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It claims effects are analyzed before causes are defined, inverting the passage''s movement from causal mechanism to documented outcome in the study described overall in sum here throughout overall in sum in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] [Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"B","text":"It establishes a cause-and-effect claim, supplies seasonal field evidence, and acknowledges limitations before drawing implications in sum in context as written here throughout overall in sum throughout overall in sum in context","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (B). Correct (B). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"C","text":"It lists technical vocabulary from the opening sentences without showing how those terms support a cumulative argument across the full paragraph from mechanism to outcome in context overall in sum in context as written.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] [Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"D","text":"It predicts that the author will publish a memoir, a motivation the passage never discusses or reasonably implies from its expository structure and academic tone as written, in a way that matches how.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] [Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
